modules.description: Provides functions to create and manage pools of preemptive threads, each maintaining a persistent local state. Operates with thread pools, promises, and stateful computations. Enables offloading long-running tasks from the Lwt event loop while preserving thread-specific context.

Provides functions to create and manage preemptive thread pools with per-thread state, execute functions within these threads, and cleanly shut them down. Operates on thread pools represented by the type 'state t, where each thread maintains its own state. Used to offload blocking operations to separate threads while maintaining access to thread-specific data during execution.
